25 LC 61 0020
House Bill 13
By: Representative Corbett of the 174th
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To provide for the compensation of the Echols County Board of Education; to provide an
2 effective date; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
4 SECTION 1.
5 The chairperson and members of the board of education of Echols County shall receive a per
6 diem of $500.000 for each day of attendance at regular meetings of the board and $50.00 for
7 each day of attendance at called meetings of the board, including training sessions of the
8 board. The total compensation for the chairperson and members of the board shall not
9 exceed $600.00 for any calendar month.
10 SECTION 2.
11 This Act shall become effective on the first day of the month following the month in which
12 it is approved by the Governor or in which it becomes law without such approval.
13 SECTION 3.
14 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
